sentences: Han Hye-ri (born August 24, 1997) is a South Korean singer and actress.
Han Hye-ri was born on August 24, 1997 in Gwangmyeong, Gyeonggi Province, South Korea.
In 2016, Han represented Star Empire Entertainment on Produce 101, a show where the final 11 contestants formed the girl group I.O.I. In the final episode, she was ranked in 12th place.
In August 2016, she joined LOEN Entertainment's project group IBI.

section: == Career == | === 2017: Acting debut and departure from Star Empire Entertainment ===

sentences: She graduated from Sinseo High School and is currently on leave of absence from studies at Paekche Institute of the Arts.
In May, Star Empire Entertainment announced that she would be debuting as a member of the group OMZM.
The group released the digital single "Molae Molae" (Korean: 몰래몰래) on August 18.
On August 19, I.B. I held a guerrilla concert 'Run to You' at Dongdaemun Design Plaza.
On September 22, I.B. I travelled to Bangkok to film their reality show Hello I.B.I.
On January 3, she signed a contract as an artist with Star Empire, but she left the agency on July 25.
